Package app.coronawarn.server.services.distribution.assembly.structure.directory

Interface IndexDirectory<T,​W extends Writable<W>>

  • Type Parameters:
    W - The specific type of Writable that this IndexDirectory can be a child of.
    T - The type of the elements in the index.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Directory<W>, Writable<W>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IndexingDecorator<T,​W>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractIndexingDecorator, DateIndexingDecorator, DiagnosisKeysCountryDirectory, DiagnosisKeysDateDirectory, DiagnosisKeysHourDirectory, HourIndexingDecorator, IndexDirectoryDecorator, IndexDirectoryOnDisk, IndexingDecoratorOnDisk
    public interface IndexDirectory<T,​W extends Writable<W>>
extends Directory<W>
    A "meta directory" that maps its on-disk subdirectories to some list of elements. This list of elements is determined by a WritableFunction.

    • Method Detail

      • addWritableToAll

        void addWritableToAll​(WritableFunction<W> writableFunction)
        Adds a writable under the name name, whose content is calculated by the writableFunction to each one of the directories created from the index. The fileFunction calculates the file content from a ImmutableStack of parent IndexDirectoryOnDisk indices. File content calculation happens on DirectoryOnDisk.write().
        Parameters:
        writableFunction - A function that can output a new writable.

      • getIndex

        Set<T> getIndex​(ImmutableStack<Object> indices)
        Calls the IndexFunction with the indices to calculate and return the elements of the index of this IndexDirectory.
        Parameters:
        indices - A ImmutableStack of parameters from all IndexDirectories further up in the hierarchy. The Stack may contain different types, depending on the types T of IndexDirectories further up in the hierarchy.

      • getIndexFormatter

        Formatter<T> getIndexFormatter()
        Returns the function used to format elements of the index (e.g. for writing to disk).
